<subSubSection pageId="95" pageNumber="96" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="95.[151,1436,1027,1268]" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1099,1124]" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Moderately large (
<quantity box="[534,647,1100,1124]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" metricValueMax="1.1" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="95" pageNumber="96" unit="mm" value="10.5" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="10.0">10–11mm</quantity>
long); pronotum and MS reddish orange, MN brown medially, orange laterally; elytra black; most similar to 
<emphasis box="[588,861,1136,1160]" italics="true" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[588,857,1136,1160]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Medeopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="95" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antennata">Medeopteryx antennata</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
distinguished by the uniformly dark antennae, the nature of the posterior margin of V7 (
<bibRefCitation author="Ballantyne, L. A. &amp; McLean, M. R." box="[571,885,1172,1196]" pageId="95" pageNumber="96" pagination="223 - 305" refId="ref122809" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. &amp; McLean, M. R. (1970) Revisional studies on the firefly genus Pteroptyx Olivier (Coleoptera: Lampyridae: Luciolinae: Luciolini). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 96, 223 - 305." type="journal article" year="1970">Ballantyne &amp; McLean 1970</bibRefCitation>
<figureCitation box="[892,974,1172,1196]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–17" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1950,1973]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,265,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-85@39.[151,1436,265,1935]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 9–17. Australoluciola anthracina type male, Cyclops (MNHN). 9, 10 dorsal (9) and ventral; 11 V6, 7 ventral; 12 pronotum dorsal; 13 type labels; 14 aedeagal sheath ventral; 15-17 aedeagus, dorsal (15), ventral (16) and lateral. These figures share scale lines: 15–17." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5265360" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5265360/files/figure.png" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
), and its restricted distribution.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
